obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (36764)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36764&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Indian Ports Act, 1908.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall extend, save as otherwise appears from its subject or context,--`
  line
  line `(a) to the ports mentioned in the first schedule, and to such parts of the navigable rivers`
  line `and channels leading to such ports respectively as have been declared to be subject to Act`
  line `XXII of 1855 (for the Regulation of Ports and Port-dues) or to the Indian Ports Act, 1875 (12`
  line `of 1875), or to the Indian Ports Act, 1889 (10 of 1889);`
  line
  line `(b) to the other ports or parts of navigable rivers or channels to which the`
  line `^1[Government], in exercise of the power hereinafter conferred, extends this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) But nothing in section 31 or section 32 shall apply to any port, river or channel to which the`
  line `section has not been specially extended by the ^1[Government].`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (36765)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Savings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36765&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act shall--`
  line
  line `(i) apply to any vessel belonging to, or in the service of, ^1[the Central Government]`
  line `or a State Government ^2*** or to any vessel of war belonging to any Foreign Prince or`
  line `State, or`
  line
  line `(ii) deprive any person of any right of property or other private right, except as hereinafter`
  line `expressly provided, or`
  line
  line `(iii) affect any law or rule relating to the customs or any order or direction lawfully`
  line `made or given pursuant thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "His Majesty".`
  line
  line `2 The words "or the Government of India" omitted by the A.O. 1937.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (36766)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36766&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or`
  line context,--
  line
  line `^1[(1) "Magistrate" means a person exercising powers under the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973`
  line `(2 of 1974);]`
  line
  line `(2) "master", when used in relation to any vessel ^2[or any aircraft making use of any`
  line `port], means, subject to the provisions of any other enactment for the time being in force,`
  line `any person (except a pilot or harbour-master ^2[of the port]) having for the time being the`
  line `charge or control of the vessel 6[or the aircraft, as the case may be];`
  line
  line `(3) "pilot" means a person for the time being authorised by the ^3[Government] to pilot vessels;`
  line
  line `(4) "port" includes also any part of a river or channel in which this Act is for the time being in`
  line force;
  line
  line `(5) "port officer" is synonymous with master-attendant;`
  line
  line `^4[(6) "ton" means a ton as determined or determinable by the rules made under`
  line `section 74 of the Merchant Shipping Act, 1958 (44 of 1958), for regulating the`
  line `measurement of the gross tonnage of ships;]`
  line
  line `(7) "vessel" includes anything made for the conveyance ^5[mainly] by water of human beings or of`
  line property;
  line
  line `^6[(8) "major port" means any port which the Central Government may by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette declare, or may under any law for the time being in force ha ve`
  line `declared, to be a major port; ^7[and]`
  line
  line `(9) "Government", as respects major ports, for all purposes, and, a s respects other`
  line `ports, for the purposes of making rules under clause (p) of section 6 (1) and of the`
  line `appointment and control of port health-officers under section 17, means the Central`
  line `Government, and save as aforesaid, means the State Government.]`
  line
  line `^8* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 1997, s. 2, for clause (1) (w.e.f. 9-1-1997).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 35 of 1951, s. 188.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Government".`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 23 of 1992, s. 2, for clause (6) (w.e.f. 24-01-1994).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 35 of 1951, s. 188.`
  line
  line `6. Added by the A.O. 1937.`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 23 of 1992, s. 2 (w.e.f. 23-1-1994).`
  line
  line `8. Clause (10) ins. by the A.O. 1950, omitted by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and Sch.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (36767)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Power to extend or withdraw the Act or certain portions thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36767&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `^1[4. Power to extend or withdraw the Act or certain portions thereof.--^(1)`
  line `2^*** The 1^[Government]`
  line `1^[Government] may, by notification in the Official Gazette,--`
  line
  line `(a) extend this Act to any port3^`
  line `in which this Act is not in force or to any part of any`
  line `navigable river or channel which leads to a port and in which this Act is not in force;`
  line
  line `(b) specially extend the provisions of section 31 or section 32 to any port to which they have not`
  line `been so extended;`
  line
  line `(c) withdraw this Act or section 31 or section 32 from any port or any part thereof in which it is`
  line `for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(2) A notification under clause (a) or clause (b) of sub-section (1) shall define the limits of the area to`
  line `which it refers.`
  line `(3) Limits defined under sub-section (2) may include any piers, jetties, landing-places,`
  line
  line `wharves, quays, docks and other works made on behalf of the public for convenience of traffic,`
  line `for safety of vessels, or for the improvement, maintenance or good government of the port and its`
  line `approaches, whether within or without high-water-mark, and, subject to any rights of private`
  line `property therein, any portion of the shore or bank within fifty yards of high-water-mark.`
  line
  line `(4) In sub-section (3) the expression “high-water-mark” means the highest point reached by ordinary`
  line `spring tides at any season of the year.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Government".`
  line `2. The words "with the previous sanction of the Governor General in Council" omitted by Act 6 of 1916, s. 2.`
  line `3. Extended to the port of MORMUGAO vide G.S.R. 1831, dated 16-11-1963.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (36768)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Alteration of limits of ports.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36768&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1[Government] may, ^2*** subject to any rights of`
  line `private property, alter the limits of any port in which this Act is in force.`
  line
  line `^3[Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the power coffered on the`
  line `Government by this sub-section includes the power to alter the limits of any port by uniting with that port`
  line `any other port or any part of any other port.]`
  line
  line `(2) When the ^4[Government] alters the limits of a port under sub-section (1), it shall declare or`
  line `describe, by notification in the Official Gazette, and by such other means, if any, as it thinks fit, the`
  line `precise extent of such limits.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Government".`
  line
  line `2. The words "with the previous sanction of the Governor General in Council and" omitted by Act 6 of 1916, s. 3.`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 17 of 1978, s. 2.`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Government".`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (36769)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Power to make port-rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36769&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1[Government] may, in addition to any rules`
  line `which it may make under any other enactment for the time being in force, make such rules,`
  line `consistent with this Act, as it thinks necessary for any of the following purposes, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) for regulating the time and hours at and during which, the speed at which, and the manner and`
  line `conditions in and on which, vessels generally or vessels of any class defined in the rules, may enter,`
  line `leave or be moved in any port subject to this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) for regulating the berths, stations and anchorages to be occupied by vessels in any such port;`
  line
  line `(c) for striking the yards and top masts, and for rigging-in the booms and yards, of`
  line `vessels in any such port, and for swinging or taking-in davits, boats and other things`
  line `projecting from such vessels;`
  line
  line `(d) for the removal or proper hanging or placing of anchors, spars and other things`
  line `being in or attached to vessels in any such port:`
  line
  line `(e) for regulating vessels whilst taking-in or discharging passengers, ballast or cargo, or any`
  line `particular kind of cargo, in any such port, and the stations to be occupied by vessels whilst so`
  line engaged;
  line
  line `^2[(ee) for regulating the manner in which oil or water mixed with oil shall be`
  line `discharged in any such port and for the disposal of the s ame;]`
  line
  line `^3[(eee) for regulating the bunkering of vessels with liquid fuel in any such port and the description`
  line `of barges, pipe lines or tank vehicles to be employed in such bunkering;]`
  line
  line `(f) for keeping free passages of such width as may be deemed necessary wit hin any`
  line `such port, and along or near to the piers, jetties, landing-places, wharves, (pays, docks,`
  line `moorings and other works in or adjoining to the same, and for marking out the spaces so to`
  line `be kept free;`
  line
  line `(g) for regulating the anchoring, fastening, mooring and unmooring of vessels in any`
  line `such port;`
  line
  line `(h) for regulating the moving and warping of all vessels within any such port and the use of warps`
  line therein;
  line
  line `(i) for regulating the use of the mooring buoys, chains and other moorings in any such port;`
  line
  line `(j) for fixing the rates to be paid ^4[in a port other than a major port] for the use of such moorings`
  line `when belonging to the ^5[Government], or of any boat, hawser or other thing belonging to the`
  line ^1[Government];
  line
  line `^6[(jj) for regulating the use of piers, jetties, landing places, wharves, quays,`
  line `warehouses and sheds when belonging to the Government;`
  line
  line `(jja) for fixing the rates to be paid for the use of piers, jetties, landing places,`
  line `wharves, quays, warehouses and sheds of any port, other than a major port, when`
  line `belonging to the Government;]`
  line
  line `^7[(k) for licensing and regulating catamarans plying for hire, and flats and cargo, passenger and`
  line `other boats plying, whether for hire or not, and whether regularly or only occasionally, in or partly`
  line `within and partly without any such port, and for licensing and regulating the crews of any such`
  line `vessels; and for determining the quantity of cargo or number of passengers or of the crew to be`
  line `carried by any such vessels and the conditions under which such vessels shall be compelled to ply for`
  line `hire, and further for the conditions under which any licence may be revoked;`
  line
  line `(kk) for providing for the fees payable in respect of the services specified in clause`
  line `(k) for any port, other than a major port;]`
  line
  line `(l) for regulating the use of fires and lights within any such port;`
  line
  line `(m) for enforcing and regultaing the use of signals or signal-lights by vessels by day or by night`
  line `in any such port;`
  line
  line `(n) for regulating the number of the crew which must be on board any vessel afloat`
  line `within the limits of any such port;`
  line
  line `(o) for regulating the employment of persons engaged in cleaning or painting vessels, or in`
  line `working in the bilges, boilers or double bottoms of vessels in any such port;`
  line
  line `^2[(p)`
  line `^3*** for the prevention of danger arising to the public health by the introduction and the`
  line `spread of any infectious or contagious disease from vessels arriving at, or being in, any such port, and`
  line `for the prevention of the conveyance of infection or contagion by means of any vessel sailing from`
  line `any such port, and in particular and without prejudice to the generality of this provision, for]--`
  line
  line `(i) the signals to be hoisted and the places of anchorage to be taken up by such vessels having`
  line `any case, or suspected case, of any infectious or contagious disease on board, or arriving at such`
  line `port from a port in which, or in the neighbourhood of which, there is believed to be, or to have`
  line `been at the time when the vessel left such port, any infectious or contagious disease;`
  line
  line `(ii) the medical inspection of such vessels and of persons on board such vessels;`
  line
  line `(iii) the questions to be answered and the information to be supplied by masters, pilots and`
  line `other persons on board such vessels;`
  line
  line `(iv) the detention of such vessels and of persons on board such vessels;`
  line
  line `(v) the duties to be performed in cases of any such disease by masters, pilots and other`
  line `persons on board such vessels;`
  line
  line `(vi) the removal to hospital or other place approved by the health-officer and the detention`
  line `therein of any person from any such vessel who is suffering or suspected to be suffering from any`
  line `such disease;`
  line
  line `(vii) the cleansing, ventilation and disinfection of such vessels or any part thereof and of any`
  line `articles therein likely to retain infection or contagion, and the destruction of rats or other vermin`
  line `in such vessels;`
  line
  line `(viii) the disposal of the dead on such vessels; and]`
  line
  line `(q) for securing the protection from heat of the officers and crew of vessels in any such port by`
  line `requiring the owner or master of any such vessel--`
  line
  line `(i) to provide curtains and double awnings for screening from the suns rays such`
  line `portions of the deck as are occupied by, or are situated immediately above, the quarters of the`
  line `officers and crew;`
  line
  line `(ii) to erect windsails so far as the existing portholes or apertures in the deck admit of their`
  line `being used for ventilating the quarters of the officers and. crew;`
  line
  line `(iii) when the deck is made of iron and not wood-sheathed, to cover with wooden planks or`
  line `other suitable non-conducting material such portions of the deck as are situated immediately`
  line `above the quarters of the officers and crew;`
  line
  line `(iv) when the quarters used by the crew and the galley are separated by an iron bulk-head`
  line `only, to furnish a temporary screen of some suitable non-conducting material between such`
  line `quarters and the galley.`
  line
  line `^10* * * * *`
  line
  line `(2) The power to make rules under sub-section (1) ^11*** is subject to the condition of the rules being`
  line `made after previous publication:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall be construed to affect the validity of any rule in force`
  line `immediately before the commencement of the Indian Ports Act, 1889 (10 of 1889) and continued by`
  line `section 2, sub-section (2), of that Act.`
  line
  line `^12[(2A) Every rule made by the State Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after`
  line `it is made, before the State Legislature.`
  line
  line `(2B) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after`
  line `it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.]`
  line
  line `(3) If any person disobeys any rule made under clause (p) of sub-section (1), he shall be punishable`
  line `for every such offence with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees.`
  line `(4) If a master fails wholly or in part to do any act prescribed by any rule made under clause`
  line `(p) of sub-section (1), the health-officer shall cause such act to be done, and the reasonable expenses`
  line `incurred in doing such act shall be recoverable by him from such master.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Government".`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 39 of 1923, s. 2.`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 9 of 1925, s. 2.`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 15 of 1997, s. 3 (w.e.f. 9-1-1997).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "Crown which had been subs. by the A.O. 1937, for Government".`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 15 of 1997, s. 3, for clause (jj) (w.e.f. 9-1-1997).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 15 of 1997, s. 3, for clause (k) (w.e.f. 9-1-1997).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 4 of 1911, s. 2, for clause (p).`
  line
  line `9. Certain words omitted by the A.O. 1937.`
  line
  line `10. Sub-section (1A) omitted by Act 26 of 1938, s. 8.Earlier inserted by Act 15 of 1922, s. 2`
  line
  line `11. The words, brackets, figure and letter and sub-section (IA) omitted by Act 26 of 1938, s. 8. Earlier inserted by`
  line `Act 15 of 1922, s. 2.`
  line
  line `12. Ins. by Act 20 of 1983, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 15-3-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (36770)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Appointment of conservator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36770&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1[Government] shall appoint some officer or body of`
  line `persons to be conservator of every port subject to this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to any direction by the ^1[Government] to the contrary,--`
  line
  line `(a) in ports where there is a port-officer, the port-officer shall be the conservator;`
  line
  line `(b) in ports where there is no port-officer, but where there is a harbour-master, the harbour-master`
  line `shall be the conservator.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the harbour-master is not conservator, the harbour-master and his assistants shall be`
  line `subordinate to, and subject to the control of, the conservator.`
  line
  line `(4) The conservator shall be subject to the control of the ^1[Government], or of any`
  line `intermediate authority which ^2[the Government] may appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Government".`
  line
  line `2. Subs., ibid., for "that Government".`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (36771)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Power of conservator to give and enforce directions for certain specified purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36771&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The conservator of any port subject to this Act may, with respect to any vessel`
  line `within the port, give directions for carrying into effect any rule for the time being in force`
  line `therein under section 6.`
  line
  line `(2) If any persons wilfully and without lawful excuse refuses or neglects to obey any lawful`
  line `direction of the conservator, after notice thereof has been given to him, he shall, for every such`
  line `offence, be punishable with fine which may extend to one hundred rupees, and in the case of a`
  line `continuing offence with a further fine which may extend to one hundred rupees for every day`
  line `during which, after such notice as aforesaid, he is proved to have wilfully and without lawful`
  line `excuse continued to disobey the direction.`
  line
  line `(3) In case of such refusal or neglect, the conservator may do, or cause to be done, all acts`
  line `necessary for the purpose of carrying the direction into execution, and may hire and employ`
  line `proper persons for that purpose, and all reasonable expenses incurred in doing such acts shal l be`
  line `recoverable by him from the person so refusing or neglecting to obey the direction.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (36772)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Power to cut warps and ropes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36772&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The conservator of any such port may, in case of urgent`
  line `necessity, cut, or cause to be cut, any warp, rope, cable or hawser endangerin g the safety of any`
  line `vessel in the port or at or near to the entrance thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (36773)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Removal of obstructions within limits of port.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36773&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The conservator may remove, or`
  line `cause to be removed, any timber, raft or other thing, floating or being in any part of any s uch`
  line `port, which in his opinion obstructs or impedes the free navigation thereof or the lawful use of`
  line `any pier, jetty, landing-place, wharf, quary, dock, mooring or other work on any part of the`
  line `shore or bank which has been declared to be within the limits of the port and is not private`
  line property.
  line
  line `(2) The owner of any such timber, raft or other thing shall be liable to pay the reasonable`
  line `expenses of the removal thereof, and if such owner or any other person has without lawful`
  line `excuse caused any such obstruction or impediment, or causes any public nuisance affecting or`
  line `likely to affect such free navigation or lawful use, he shall also be punishable with fine which`
  line `may extend to one hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `(3) The conservator or any Magistrate having jurisdiction over the offence may cause any such`
  line `nuisance to be abated.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (36774)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Recovery of expenses of removal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36774&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `If the owner of any such timber, raft or other thing,`
  line `or the person who has caused any such obstruction, impediment or public nuisance as is`
  line `mentioned in the last foregoing section, neglects to pay the reasonable expenses incurred in the`
  line `removal thereof, within one week after demand, or within fourteen days after such removal has`
  line `been notified in the Official Gazette or in such other manner as the ^1[Government] by general or`
  line `special order directs, the conservator may cause such timber, raft or other thing, or the materials`
  line `of any public nuisance so removed, or so much thereof as may be necessary, to be sold by`
  line `public auction;`
  line
  line `and may retain all the expenses of such removal and sale out of the proceeds of the sale,`
  line `and shall pay the surplus of such proceeds, or deliver so much of the thing or materials as`
  line `may remain unsold, to the person entitled to receive the same;`
  line
  line `and, if no such person appears, shall cause the same to be kept and deposited in such manner as the`
  line `^1[Government] directs;`
  line
  line `and may, if necessary, from time to time, realise the expenses of keeping the same, together`
  line `with the expenses of sale, by a further sale of so much of the thing or materials as may remain`
  line unsold.
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (36775)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Removal of lawful obstructions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36775&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any obstruction or impediment to the navigation of any`
  line `port subject to this Act has been lawfully made, or has become lawful by reason of the long continuance`
  line `of such obstruction or impediment, or otherwise, the conservator shall report the same for the information of the ^1[Government], and shall, with the sanction of ^2[the Government], cause the same to be removed or`
  line `altered, making reasonable compensation to the person suffering damage by such removal or alteration.`
  line
  line `(2) Any dispute arising concerning such compensation shall be determined according to the law`
  line `relating to like disputes in the case of land required for public purposes.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Government".`
  line
  line `2. Subs., ibid., for "that Government".`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (36776)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Fouling of Government moorings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36776&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any vessel hooks or gets foul of any of the`
  line `buoys or moorings laid down by or by the authority of the ^1[Government] in any such port, the`
  line `master of such vessel shall not, nor shall any other person, except in case of emergency, lift the`
  line `buoy or mooring for the purpose of unhooking or getting clear from the same without the`
  line `assistance of the conservator;`
  line
  line `and the conservator, immediately on receiving notice of such accident, shall assist and`
  line `superintend the clearing of such vessel;`
  line
  line `and the master of such vessel shall, upon demand, pay such reasonable expenses as may be incurred`
  line `in clearing the same.`
  line
  line `(2) Any master or other person offending against the provisions of this section shall, for`
  line `every such offence, be punishable with fine which may extend to one hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (36777)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Raising or removal of wreck impeding navigation within limits of port.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36777&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) If any vessel is wrecked, stranded or sunk in any port in such a manner as to`
  line `impede or likely to impede any navigation thereof, the conservator shall give notice to the`
  line `owner of the vessel to raise, remove or destroy the vessel within such period as may be`
  line `specified in the notice and to furnish such adequate security to the satisfaction of the`
  line `conservator to ensure that the vessel shall be raised, removed or destroyed within the said`
  line `period:`
  line
  line `Provided that the conservator may extend such period to such further period as he may`
  line `consider necessary having regard to the circumstances of such case and the extent of its`
  line `impediment to navigation.`
  line
  line `(1A) Where the owner of any vessel to whom a notice has been issued under`
  line `sub-section (1) fails to raise, remove or destroy such vessel within the period specified in the`
  line `notice or the extended period or fails to furnish the security required of him, the conservator`
  line `may cause the vessel to be raised, removed or destroyed.`
  line
  line `(1B) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing sub-sections, if the conservator is of the`
  line `opinion that any vessel which is wrecked, stranded or sunk in any port is required to be immediately`
  line `raised, removed or destroyed for the purpose of uninterrupted navigation in such port, he may, without`
  line `giving any notice under sub-section (1), cause the vessel to be raised, removed or destroyed.]`
  line
  line `(2) If any property recovered by a conservator acting ^2[under sub-section (1A) or`
  line `sub-section (1B)] is unclaimed or the person claiming it fails to pay the reasonable expenses`
  line `incurred by the conservator under that sub-section and a further sum of twenty per cent. of the`
  line `amount of such expenses, the conservator may sell the property by public auction, if the`
  line `property is of a perishable nature, forthwith, and, if it is not of a perishable nat ure, at any time`
  line `not less than ^3[thirty days] after the recovery thereof.`
  line
  line `(3) The expenses and further sum aforesaid shall be payable to the conservator out of the`
  line `sale-proceeds of the property, and the balance shall be paid to the person entitled to the property`
  line `recovered, or, if no such person appears and claims the balance, shall be held in deposit for payment,`
  line `without interest, to any person thereafter establishing his right thereto:`
  line
  line `Provided that the person makes his claim within three years from the date of the sale.`
  line
  line `^4[(4) Where the sale proceeds of the property are not sufficient to meet the expenses and further`
  line `sum aforesaid, the owner of the vessel at the time the vessel was wrecked, stranded or sunk shall`
  line `be liable to pay the deficiency to the conservator on demand, and if the deficiency be not paid`
  line `within one month of such demand the conservator may recover the deficiency from such owner in`
  line `the manner laid down in sub-section (2) of section 57 for recovery of expenses and damages or in`
  line `any other manner according as the deficiency does not or does exceed one thousand rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 1992, s. 3, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 12-8-1992).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "under sub-section (1)" (w.e.f. 12-8-1992).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "two months" (w.e.f. 12-8-1992).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 55 of 1952, s. 2.`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (36778)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Power to board vessels and enter buildings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36778&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The conservator or any of his assistants may,`
  line `whenever he suspects that any offence against this Act has been, or is about to be, committed, or`
  line `whenever it is necessary for him so to do in the performance of any duty imposed upon him by this Act,`
  line
  line `and the person appointed under this Act to receive any port dues, fees or other charges`
  line `payable in respect of any vessel, may, whenever it is necessary for him so to do in the`
  line `performance of any duty imposed upon him by this Act,`
  line
  line `either alone or with any other person, board any vessel, or enter any building or place, within the`
  line `limits of any port subject to this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) If the master of the vessel, or any person in possession or occupation of the building or place,`
  line `without lawful excuse, refuses to allow any such person as is mentioned in sub-section (1) to board`
  line `or enter such vessel, building or place in the performance of any duty imposed upon him by this Act,`
  line `he shall for every such offence be punishable with fine which may extend to two hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (36779)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Power to require crews to prevent or extinguish fire.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36779&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of preventing or`
  line `extinguishing fire in any port subject to this Act, the conservator or port-officer may require the master of`
  line `any vessel within the port to place at his disposal such number as he requires, not exceeding three-fourths,`
  line `of the crew then under the order of such master.`
  line
  line `(2) Any master refusing or neglecting to comply with such requisition shall be punishable with`
  line `fine which may extend to five hundred rupees, and any seaman then under his orders who, after`
  line `being directed by the master to obey the orders of the conservator or port-officer for the purpose`
  line `aforesaid, refuses to obey such orders, shall be punishable with fine which may extend to`
  line `twenty-five rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (36780)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Appointment and powers of health-officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36780&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1[Government] may appoint at any port`
  line `subject to this Act an officer to be called the health-officer.`
  line
  line `(2) A health-officer shall, subject to the control of the ^1[Government], have the following powers,`
  line `within the limits of the port for which he is appointed, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) with respect to any vessel, the powers conferred on a shipping-master by the Indian Merchant`
  line `Shipping Act, 1859^2 (1 of 1859), section 71;`
  line
  line `(b) power to enter on board any vessel and medically examine all or any of the seamen or`
  line `apprentices on board the vessel;`
  line
  line `(c) power to require and enforce the production of the log-book and any other books, papers or`
  line `documents which he thinks necessary for the purpose of enquiring into the health and medical`
  line `condition of the persons on board the vessel;`
  line
  line `(d) power to call before him and question for any such purpose all or any of those persons and to`
  line `require true answers to any questions which he thinks fit to ask;`
  line
  line `(e) power to require any person so questioned to make and subscribe a declaration of the truth of`
  line `the statements made by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Government".`
  line
  line `2. See now the Merchant Shipping Act, 1958 (44 of 1958).`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (36781)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Indemnity of Government against act or default of port -official or pilot.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36781&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The Government`
  line `shall not be responsible for any act or default of any conservator, port-officer or harbour-master, of any port subject to this Act, or of any deputy or assistant of any of the authorities aforesaid, or of any person`
  line `acting under the control or direction of any such authority, deputy or assistant, or for any act or default of`
  line `any pilot, or for any damage sustained by any vessel in consequence of any defect in any of the moorings,`
  line `hawsers or other things belonging to the Government which may be used by the vessel:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall protect ^1[the Government] from a suit in respect of any act`
  line `done by or under the express order or sanction of the Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "the Secretary of State for India in Council" successively subs. by the A.O. 1937 and the A.O. 1950,`
  line `to read as above.`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (36782)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Injuring buoys, beacons and moorings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36782&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall, without lawful excuse, lift, injure,`
  line `loosen or set adrift any buoy, beacon or mooring fixed or laid down by, or by the authority of, the`
  line `^1[Government], in any port subject to this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person offends against the provisions of this section, he shall for every such offence be`
  line `laible, in addition to the payment of the amount of damage done, to fine which may extend to two`
  line `thousand rupees, or to imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years.`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (36783)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Wilfully loosening vessel from moorings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36783&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `If any person wilfully and without lawful excuse`
  line `loosens or removes from her moorings any vessel within any such port without leave or authority from`
  line `the owner or master of the vessel, he shall, for every such offence, be punishable with fine which may`
  line `extend to two hundred rupees, or with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (36784)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Improperly discharging ballast.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36784&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) No ballast or rubbish, and no other thing likely to form a`
  line `bank or shoal or to be detrimental to navigation, shall, without lawful excuse, be cast or thrown into any`
  line `such port or into or upon any place on shore from which the same is liable to be washed into any such`
  line `port, either by ordinary or high tides, or by storms or land-floods ^2[and no oil or water mixed with oil`
  line `shall be discharged in or into any such port, to which any rules made under clause (ee) of sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 6 apply, otherwise than in accordance with such rules].`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who by himself or another so casts or throws any ballast or rubbish or any such other`
  line `thing ^2[or so discharges any oil or water mixed with oil], and the master of any vessel from which the`
  line `same is so cast, ^3[thrown or discharged], shall be punishable with fine which may extend to ^4[five lakh`
  line `rupees], and shall pay any reasonable expenses which may be incurred in removing the same.`
  line
  line `(3) If, after receiving notice from the conservator of the port to desist from so casting or throwing any`
  line `ballast or rubbish or such other thing ^2[or from so discharging any oil or water mixed with oil], any master`
  line `continues so to cast, ^5[throw or discharge] the same, he shall also be liable to simple imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to ^6[one year] and to fine which may extend to five lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in this section applies to any case in which the ballast or rubbish or such other thing is`
  line `cast or thrown into ^7[or the oil or water mixed with oil is discharged in or into] any such port with the`
  line `consent in writing of the conservator, or within any limits within which such act may be authorised by the`
  line ^1[Government].
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Government".`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 39 of 1923, s. 3.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "or thrown".`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 23 of 1992, s. 4, for "five hundred rupees" (w.e.f. 12-8-1992).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 39 of 1923, s. 3, for "or throw it".`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 23 of 1992, s. 4, for "two months" (w.e.f. 12-8-1992).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 39 of 1923, s. 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (36785)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Graving vessel within prohibited limits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36785&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `If any person graves, breams or smokes any vessel`
  line `in any such port, contrary to the directions of the conservator, or at any time or within any limits at or within which such act is prohibited by the ^1[Government], he and the master of the vessel shall for`
  line `every such offence be punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees each.`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (36838)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Boiling pitch on board vessel within prohibited limits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36838&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `If any person boils or heats any`
  line `pitch, tar, resin, dammer, turpentine, oil, or other such combustible matter on board any vessel within`
  line `any such port, or at any place within its limits where such act is prohibited by the ^1[Government], or`
  line `contrary to the directions of the conservator, he and the master of the vessel shall for every such`
  line `offence be punishable with fine which may extend to two hundred rupees each.`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (36788)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Drawing spirits by unprotected artificial light.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36788&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `If any person, by an unprotected artificial`
  line `light, draws off spirits on board any vessel within any port subject to this Act, he and the master of the`
  line `vessel shall for every such offence be punishable with fine which may extend to two hundred rupees each.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (36789)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title Warping.
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36789&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every master of a vessel in any port subject to this Act shall, when required`
  line `so to do by the conservator, permit warps or hawsers to be made fast to the vessel for the purpose of`
  line `warping any other vessel in the port, and shall not allow any such warp or hawser to be let go until`
  line `required so to do.`
  line
  line `(2) A master offending against sub-section (1) shall be punishable for every such offence with fine`
  line `which may extend to two hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (36790)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Leaving out warp or hawser after sunset.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36790&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) A master of a vessel shall not cause or`
  line `suffer any warp or hawser attached to his vessel to be left out in any port subject to this Act after`
  line `sunset in such a manner as to endanger the safety of any other vessel navigating in the port.`
  line
  line `(2) A master offending against sub-section (1) shall be punishable for every such offence with fine`
  line `which may extend to two hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (36791)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Discharge of fire-arms in port.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36791&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `If any person, without lawful excuse, discharges any firearm in`
  line `any port subject to this Act, or on or from any pier, landing place, warp or quay thereof, except a gun`
  line `loaded only with gunpowder for the purpose of making a signal of distress, or for such other purpose as`
  line `may be allowed by the ^1[Government], he shall for every such offence be punishable with fine which may`
  line `extend to fifty rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (36792)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Penalty on master omitting to take order to extinguish fire.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36792&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `If the master of any vessel in`
  line `which fire takes place while lying in any such port wilfully omits to take order to extinguish the fire or`
  line `obstructs the conservator or the port-officer, or any person acting under the authority of the conservator or`
  line `port-officer, in extinguishing or attempting to extinguish the fire, he shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees or`
  line `with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (36793)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Unauthorised person not to search for lost stores.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36793&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person, without the permission of`
  line `the conservator, shall, in any port subject to this Act, creep or sweep for anchors, cables or other stores`
  line `lost or supposed to be lost therein.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person offends against the provisions of sub-section (1), he shall be punishable with fine`
  line `which may extend to one hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (36794)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Removing stones or injuring shores of port prohibited.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36794&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person without the permission`
  line `of the conservator shall in any port subject to this Act remove or carry away any rock, stones, shingle,`
  line `gravel, sand or soil or any artificial protection from any part of the bank or shore of the port;`
  line
  line `and no person shall sink or bury in any part of such bank or shore, whether the same is public`
  line `or private property, any mooring-post, anchor or any other thing, or do any other thing which is`
  line `likely to injure or to be used so as to injure such bank or shore, except with the permission of the`
  line `conservator, and with the aid or under the inspection of such person, if any, as the conservator may`
  line `appoint to take part in or overlook the performance of such work.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person offends against sub-section (1), he shall for every such offence be punishable with`
  line `fine which may extend to one hundred rupees and shall pay any reasonable expenses which may be`
  line `incurred in repairing any injury done by him to the bank or shore.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (36795)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Moving of vessels without pilot or permission of harbour-master.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36795&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) No vessel of`
  line `the measurement of two hundred tons or upwards shall enter, leave or be moved in any port to`
  line `which this section has been specially extended without having a pilot, harbour-master or assistant`
  line `of the port-officer or harbour-master on board;`
  line
  line `^1[and no mechanically propelled vessel of any measurement less than two hundred tons and no`
  line `other vessel of any measurement less than two hundred tons] and exceeding one hundred tons shall`
  line `enter, leave or be moved in any such port without having a pilot, harbour-master or assistant of the`
  line `port-officer or harbour-master on board, unless authority in writing so to do has been obtained from`
  line `the conservator or some officer empowered by him to give such authority.`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that the ^3[Government] may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that in any port`
  line `specified in such notification the provisions of this sub-section shall not apply to sailing vessels of any`
  line `measurement not exceeding a measurement so specified.]`
  line
  line `^4[(2) Notwithstanding anything in sub-section (1), the owner or master of a vessel which is by`
  line `that sub-section required to have a pilot, harbour-master or assistant of the port-officer or harbourmaster on board, shall be answerable for- any loss or damage caused by the vessel or by any fault`
  line `of the navigation of the vessel, in the same manner as he would have been if he had not been so`
  line `required by that sub-section:`
  line
  line `Provided that the provisions of this sub-section shall not take effect till the first day of January,`
  line `1918, or such earlier date as the Central Government may notify in that behalf in the Official`
  line Gazette.]
  line
  line `^5[(3)] If any vessel, except in case of urgent necessity, enters, leaves or is moved in the port contrary`
  line `to the provisions of sub-section (1), the master of the vessel shall for every such offence be punishable`
  line `with fine which may extend to two hundred rupees, unless upon application to the proper officer the`
  line `master was unable to procure a pilot, harbour-master or assistant of the port-officer or harbour-master to`
  line `go on board the vessel.`
  line
  line `^6* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 55 of 1952, s. 3, for certain words.`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 36 of 1925, s. 2.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Governor-General in Council".`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 6 of 1916, s. 5.`
  line
  line `5. Sub-sections (2), (3) and (4) re-numbered as sub-sections (3), (4) and (5) respectively by s. 5, ibid.`
  line
  line `6. Sub-sections (4) and (5), as re-numbered by Act 6 of 1916, s. 5, omitted by Act 36 of 1925, s. 2.`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (36796)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Provision of certain vessels with fire-extinguishing apparatus.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36796&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every vessel exceeding`
  line `the measurement of two hundred tons and lying in any port to which this section has been specially`
  line `extended shall be provided with a proper force pump and hose and appurtenances, for the purpose of`
  line `extinguishing any fire which may occur on board.`
  line
  line `(2) The master of such a vessel who, having been required by the conservator to comply with`
  line `the provisions of sub-section (1), neglects or rufuses, without lawful excuse, so to do for the space`
  line `of seven days after such requisition, shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five`
  line `hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (36797)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Levy of port-dues.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36797&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `^1[Subject to the, provisions of sub-section (2)], in each of the`
  line `ports mentioned in the first schedule ^2[other than a major port] such port-due, not exceeding the`
  line `amount specified for the port in the third column of the schedule as the ^3[Government], directs,`
  line `shall be levied on vessels entering the port and described in the second column of the schedule,`
  line `but not oftener than the time fixed for the port in the fourth column of the schedule.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) The ^3[Government] may, by notification in the Official Gazette, alter or add to any`
  line `entry in the first schedule relating to ports ^4[in ^5[any State] or, as the case may be, in the State],`
  line `and this power shall include the power to regroup any such ports:`
  line
  line `^6* * * * *`
  line
  line `^7[(3)] Whenever the ^1[Government], ^8*** declares any other port ^2[other than a major port] to be`
  line `subject to this Act, it may, ^9*** by the same or any subsequent declaration, further declare,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the terms of any of the entries in the second column of the first schedule the`
  line `vessels which are to be chargeable with port-dues on entering the port,`
  line
  line `(b) the highest rates at which such dues may be levied in respect of vessels chargeable therewith,`
  line and
  line
  line `(c) the times at which such vessels are to be so chargeable.`
  line
  line `^10* * * * *`
  line
  line `^7[(4)] All port-dues now leviable in any port shall continue to be so leviable until it is`
  line `otherwise declared in exercise of the powers conferred by this section.`
  line
  line `^7[(5)] An order increasing or imposing port-dues under this section shall not take effect till`
  line `the expiration of ^11[thirty days] from the day on which the order was published in the Official`
  line Gazette.
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 6 of 1916, s. 6.`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 15 by 1997, s. 4 (w.e.f. 9-1-1997).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Government."`
  line
  line `4. subs., ibid., for "within its own province."`
  line
  line `5. The words "British India" successively subs. by the A.O. 1948; and the A.O. 1950 to read as above.`
  line
  line `6. Proviso omitted by the A.O. 1937.`
  line
  line `7. Sub-sections (2), (3) and (4) re-numbered as sub-sections (3), (4) and (5) respectively by Act 6 of 1916, s. 6.`
  line
  line `8. Certain words omitted by Act 6 of 1916, s. 6.`
  line
  line `9. The words "with the like sanction" omitted by s. 6, ibid.`
  line
  line `10. The proviso ins. by s. 6, ibid. Earlier omitted by the A.O. 1937.`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by Act 23 of 1992, s. 5, for "sixty days" (w.e.f. 12-8-1992).`
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (36798)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Variation of port-dues by Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 1997, s. 5, for s. 34 (w.e.f. 9-1-1997).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36798&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `^1[34. Variation of port dues by Government.--The Government may after consulting,--`
  line
  line `(a) in case of ports other than major ports, the authority appointed under section 36;`
  line
  line `(b) in case of major ports, the Authority constituted under section 47A of the Major Port Trusts`
  line `Act, 1963 (38 of 1963),`
  line
  line `exempt, subject to such conditions, if any, as it thinks fit to impose, any vessel or class of vessels`
  line `entering a port subject to this Act from payment of port-dues and cancel the exemption, or may`
  line `vary the rates at which port dues are to be fixed in the port, in such manner as, having regard to`
  line `the receipts and charges on account of the port it thinks expedient, by reducing or raising the`
  line `dues, or any of them or may extend the periods for which any vessel or class of vessels entering a`
  line `port shall be exempt from liability to pay port-dues:`
  line
  line `Provided that the rates shall not in any case exceed the amount authorized to be taken by or under this`
  line Act.]
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (36799)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Fees for pilotage and certain other services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36799&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) Within any port subject to this Act`
  line `^1[not being a major port], fees may be charged for pilotage, hauling' mooring, re-mooring,`
  line `hooking, measuring and other services rendered to vessels, at such rates as the ^2[Government],`
  line `may direct:`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(2) The fees now chargeable for such services shall continue to be chargeable unless and until they`
  line `are altered in exercise of the power conferred by sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `^4[(3) The Government may, in special cases, remit the whole or any portion of the fees`
  line `chargeable under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2).`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 1997, s. 6 (w.e.f. 9-1-1997).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Government".`
  line
  line `3. The original proviso was omitted by Act 6 of 1916, s. 8, and the proviso ins. by Act 11 of 1929, s. 3, omitted by the`
  line `A.O. 1937.`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 35 of 1951, s. 190.`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (36800)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Receipt, expenditure and account of port-charges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36800&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1[Government] shall`
  line `appoint some officer or body of persons at every port at which any dues, fees or other`
  line `charges are authorised to be taken by or under this Act to receive the same and, subject to the`
  line `control of the ^1[Government], to expend the receipts on any of the objects authorised by this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(2) Such officer or body shall keep for the port a distinct account, to be called the port`
  line `fund account, showing, in such detail as the ^1[Government] prescribes, the receipts and`
  line `expenditure of the port, and shall publish annually as soon after the first day of April as may`
  line `be practicable an abstract, in such form as ^2[the Government] prescribes, of the account for`
  line `the past financial year:`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that the port fund account for any port may, if so authorised under the provisions`
  line `of any Act relating to such port, be merged with the general account of that port, and in such a`
  line `case, the provisions of sub-section (6) shall not apply and the provisions of sub-sections (4) and`
  line `(5) shall have effect as if for the words "the port fund account of the port" therein, the words`
  line `"the general account of the port" had been substituted.]`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
  line
  line `(4) All money received under this Act at or on account of any port subject to this Act,`
  line `excluding receipts on account of pilotage but including -`
  line
  line `^5[(a) fines other than those creditable to the pilotage. account of the port under`
  line `sub-section (5a)],`
  line
  line `(b) proceeds of waifs, and`
  line
  line `(c) any balance of the proceeds of a sale under section 14 where no right to the`
  line `balance has been established on a claim made within three years from the date of the`
  line sale,
  line
  line `shall be credited in the port fund account of the port.`
  line
  line `(5) All expenses incurred for the sake of any such port, excluding expenses on account of pilotage`
  line `but including--`
  line
  line `(a) the pay and allowances of all persons upon the establishment of the port,`
  line
  line `(b) the cost of buoys, becons, lights and all other works maintained chiefly for the benefit`
  line `of vessels being in or entering or leaving the port or passing through the rivers or channels`
  line `leading thereto,`
  line
  line `(c) pensions, allowances and gratuities of persons who have been employed in the port under this`
  line `or any other enactment relating to ports and port dues, or such portion of those pensions, allowances`
  line `and gratuities as the ^6[Government] may by rule determine.`
  line
  line `(d) with the previous sanction of the ^6[Government], contributions towards the support of`
  line `public hospitals or dispensaries suitable for the receiption or relief of seamen or otherwise towards`
  line `the provision of sanitary superinendence and medical aid for the shipping in the port and for`
  line `seamen whether ashore or afloat, belonging to vessels in the port, and`
  line
  line `(e) with the like sanction, contributions towards sailors homes, institutes, rest-houses and coffeehouses and for other purposes connected with the health, recreation and temporal well-being of`
  line sailors,
  line
  line `shall be charged to the port fund account of the port.`
  line
  line `^7[(5a) All fees charged for pilotage at any port subject to this Act ^8[other than a major port] and`
  line `all fines and penalties levied under the Act or under any other Act relating to the port from pilots or`
  line `other persons employed in the pilot service other than fines and penalties imposed by a court, shall`
  line `be credited to a distinct account to be called the pilotage account of the port.`
  line
  line `(5b) All sums so credited to the pilotage account may be applied, in such proportions as the`
  line `Government may from time to time direct, to the following purposes, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the purchase and maintenance in repair of such vessels, and the supply of such materials,`
  line `stores or other things as the officer or body appointed under sub-section (1) may deem it necessary to`
  line `purchase, maintain or supply for the efficiency of the pilot service;`
  line
  line `(b) the payment of the salaries, wages and allowances of pilots and other persons employed in the`
  line `pilot service or in the supervision thereof:`
  line
  line `(c) the payment of pensions, retiring gratuities, compassionate allowances or bonuses to pilots`
  line `and other persons engaged in the pilot service, and of the contributions, if any, duly authorised to be`
  line `made in their behalf to any provident fund or welfare fund;`
  line
  line `(d) the payment of pensions, gratuities and compassionate allowances granted by the`
  line `officer or body appointed under sub-section (1) to pilots and other persons engaged in the`
  line `pilot service who have been injured in the execution of their duty and to the surviving`
  line `relatives of pilots and other persons so engaged who have been killed in the execution of their`
  line `duty or who may die while still in the service of such officer or body;`
  line
  line `(e) the provision of educational, recreational and other amenities for pilots and other persons`
  line `employed in the pilot service;`
  line
  line `(f) the payment of contributions or appropriations to any special fund or funds established`
  line `under the provisions of any other Act relating to the port to which the officer or body`
  line `appointed under sub-section (1) considers contributions or appropriations should be made`
  line `from the pilotage account;`
  line
  line `(g) any other expenditure which may, with the previous sanction of the Government, be incurred`
  line `in respect of the pilot service.`
  line
  line `(5c) If the officer or body appointed under sub-section (1) at any port is also the authority`
  line `responsible for maintaining the general account of the port, then notwithstanding the absence of`
  line `any provision in that behalf in the Act under which such general account is maintained, such`
  line `officer or body may, with the previous sanction of the Government, apply any sum out of the`
  line `moneys credited to such general account towards meeting deficits, if any, in the pilotage account of`
  line `the port, or transfer the whole or any part of any surplus funds, in the pilotage account to the`
  line `general account of the port.]`
  line
  line `(6) Subject to the provisions of any local law as to the disposal of any balance from time to time`
  line `standing to the credit of a port fund account ^9[or of a pilotage account], any such balance may be`
  line `temporarily invested in such manner as the ^10[Government], may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Government".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "that Government".`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 35 of 1951, s. 191.`
  line
  line `4 Sub-section (3) omitted by Act 6 of 1916, s. 9.`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 35 of 1951, s. 191, for cl. (a).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Government".`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 35 of 1951, 8. 191.`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 23 of 1992, s. 6`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by Act 35 of 1951, s. 191.`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Government".`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (36801)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Grouping of ports.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36801&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may direct that for the purposes of the last`
  line `foregoing section any number of ports ^1[in the State not being major ports] shall be regarded as`
  line `constituting a single port, and thereupon all moneys to be credited to the port fund account under`
  line `sub-section (4) of that section shall form a common port fund account which shall be available for`
  line `the payment of all expenses incurred for the sake of any of the ports:`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `(2) Where ports are grouped by or under this Act, the following consequences ensue, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the State Government, in the exercise of its control over expenditure debitable to the`
  line `common port fund account of the group, may, ^3*** make rules with respect to the expenditure`
  line `of the fund for the sake of the several ports of the group on the objects authorised by this Act`
  line `^3***; and`
  line
  line `(b) by the State Government may exercise its authority under section 34 as regards all the ports in`
  line `the group collective by or as regards any of them separately`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins., ibid.`
  line
  line `2. The proviso omitted, ibid.`
  line
  line `3. Certain words omitted, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (36802)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Receipts for port-charges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36802&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `The person to whom any dues, fees or other charges`
  line `authorized to be taken by or under this Act are paid shall grant to the person paying the same a`
  line `proper voucher in writing under his hand, describing the name of his office, the port or place at`
  line `which the dues, fees or other charges are paid, and the name, tonnage and other proper description`
  line `of the vessel in respect of which the payment is made.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (36803)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Master to report arrival.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes `1. Certain words omitted by the A.O. 1948.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36803&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) Within twenty-four hours after the arrival within the limits`
  line `of any port subject to this Act of any vessel liable to the payment of port-dues under this Act, the`
  line `master of the vessel shall report her arrival to the conservator of the port.`
  line
  line `(2) A master failing without lawful excuse to make such report within the time aforesaid shall for`
  line `every such offence be punishable with fine which may extend to one hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section applies to tug-steamers, ferry steamers or river steamers plying to and from`
  line `any of the ports subject this Act.^1***`
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (36804)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Conservator may in certain cases ascertain draught and charge expense to master.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36804&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `If any`
  line `vessel liable to the payment of port-dues is in any such port without proper marks on the stem and stern`
  line `posts thereof for denoting her draught, the conservator may cause the same to be ascertained by means of`
  line `the operation of hooking, and the master of the vessel shall be liable to pay the expenses of the operation.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (36805)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Ascertainment of tonnage of vessel liable to port -dues.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36805&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `In order to ascertain the tonnage of`
  line `any vessel liable to pay port-dues the following rules shall be observed, namely:--`
  line
  line `(1) (a) If the vessel is a British registered vessel or a vessel registered under the Indian`
  line `registration of Ships Act, 1841 (10 of 1841), or the Indian Registration of Ships Act, (1841)`
  line `Amendment Act, 1850 (11 of 1850), or under any other law for the time being in force for the`
  line `registration of vessels in ^1[India], the conservator may require the owner or master of the vessel`
  line `or any person having possession of her register to produce the register for inspection.`
  line
  line `(b) if the owner or master or such person neglects or refuses to produce the register or`
  line `otherwise to satisfy the conservator as to what is the true tonnage of the vessel in respect of`
  line `which the port-dues are payable, he shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one`
  line `hundred rupees, and the conservator may cause the vessel to be measured, and the tonnage`
  line `thereof to be ascertained, according to the mode of measurement prescribed by the rules for the`
  line `time being in force for regulating the measurement of British vessels, and in such case the`
  line `owner or master of the vessel shall also be liable to pay the expenses of the measurement.`
  line
  line `(2) If the vessel is not a British registered vessel or a vessel registered under the Indian`
  line `Registration of Ships Act, 1841 (10 of 1841), or the Indian Registration of Ships Act (1841)`
  line `Amendment Act, 1850 (11 of 1850), or under any other law for the time being in force for the`
  line `registration of vessels in ^2[India], and the owner or master thereof fails to satisfy the conservator`
  line `as to what is her true tonnage according to the mode of measurement prescribed by the rules for`
  line `the time being in force for regulating the measurement of British vessels, the conservator shall`
  line `cause the vessel to be measured' and the tonnage thereof to be ascertained, according to the mode`
  line `aforesaid, and in such case the owner or master of the vessel shall be liable to pay the expenses`
  line `of the measurement.`
  line
  line `(3) If the vessel is a vessel of which the tonnage cannot be ascertained according to the mode of`
  line `measurement mentioned in clauses (1) and (2), the tonnage of the vessel shall be determined by the`
  line `conservator on such an estimate as may seem to him to be just.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "British India" successively amended by the A.O. 1948, the A.O. 1950 and Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and Sch., to read as`
  line above.
  line
  line `2. The words "British India" successively amended by the A.O. 1948, the A.O. 1950 and Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and Sch., to read as above.`
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (36806)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Distraint and sale on refusal to pay port-charges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes `1. The proviso inserted by Act 23 of 1992, s. 7 (w.e.f. 12-8-1992).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36806&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `If the master of any vessel in respect of`
  line `which any port-dues, fees or other charges are payable under this Act, refuses or neglects to pay the`
  line `same on demand, the authority appointed to receive such port-dues, fees or other charges may`
  line `distrain or arrest the vessel, and the tackle, apparel and furniture belonging thereto or any part`
  line `thereof, and detain the same until the amount due is paid;`
  line
  line `and in case any part of the port-dues, fees or other charges or of the costs of the distress or`
  line `arrest or of the keeping of the vessel or other thing distrained or arrested remains unpaid for the`
  line `space of five days next after any such distress or arrest, may cause the vessel or other thing`
  line `distrained or arrested to be sold, and with the proceeds of such sale may satisfy the port-dues, fees`
  line `or other charges and the costs including the costs of the remaining unpaid, and shall render the`
  line `surplus, if any, to the master of the vessel upon demand.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that where such vessel or other thing is already arrested under the order of a court or other`
  line `authority, the authority appointed to receive port-dues, fees or other charges, may sell the vessel or other`
  line `thing only with the prior permission of such court or other authority and satisfy the port-dues, fees or`
  line `other charges and the costs including costs of sale remaining unpaid, and disburse the surplus, if any, in`
  line `accordance with the orders or directions of such court or other authority:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the person to whom the vessel or other thing is sold under this section shall`
  line `be deemed to be the owner thereof and registered as such under the Merchant Shipping Act, 1958].`
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (36807)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `No port-clearance to be granted until port-charges are paid.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36807&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `The officer of`
  line `Government whose duty it is to grant a port-clearance for any vessel shall not grant such clearance--`
  line
  line `(a) until her owner or master, or some other person, has paid or secured to the satisfaction of`
  line `such officer the amount of all port-dues, fees and other charges, and of all fines, penalties and`
  line `expenses to which the vessel or her owner or master is liable under this Act,`
  line
  line `(b) until all expenses, which by the Merchant Shiping Act, 1894 (57 & 58 Vict., c. 60.), section`
  line `207, are to be borne by her owner incurred since her arrival in the port from which he seeks clearance,`
  line `have been paid.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (36808)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Port-charges payable in one port recoverable at any other port.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36808&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the master of any`
  line `vessel in respect of which any such sum as is mentioned in the last foregoing section is payable causes her to leave any port without having paid the sum, the authority appointed to receive port-dues, fees and other`
  line `charges at the port under this Act may require in writing the authority appointed to receive port-dues, fees`
  line `and other charges under this Act at any other port in ^1[India] to which she may proceed, or in which she`
  line `may be, to levy the sum.`
  line
  line `(2) The authority to whom the requisition is directed shall proceed to levy such sum in the`
  line `manner prescribed in section 42, and a certificate purporting to be made by the authority appointed to`
  line `receive port-dues, fees and other charges at the port where such sum as is mentioned in the last`
  line `foregoing section became payable, statingthe amount payable, shall be sufficient prima facie proof`
  line `of such amount in any proceeding under section 42 and also (in case the amount payable is disputed)`
  line `in any subsequent proceeding under section 59.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "British India" successively amended by the A.O. 1948, the A.O. 1950 and Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and`
  line `Schedule to read as above.`
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (36809)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Penalty for evading payment of port-charges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36809&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the master of a vessel evades the`
  line `payment of any such sum as is mentioned in section 43, he shall be punishable with fine which may`
  line `extend to five times the amount of the sum.`
  line
  line `(2) In any proceeding before a Magistrate on a prosecution under sub-section (1), any such certificate`
  line `as is mentioned in section 44, sub-section (2), stating that the master has evaded such payment, shall be`
  line `sufficient prima facie proof of the evasion, unless the master shows to the satisfaction of the Magistrate`
  line `that the departure of the vessel without payment of the sum was caused by stress of weather, or that there`
  line `was lawful or reasonable ground for such departure.`
  line
  line `(3) Any Magistrate having jurisdiction under this Act in any port to which the vessel may proceed, or`
  line `in which she may he found, shall be deemed to have jurisdiction in any proceeding under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (36810)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Port-due on vessels in ballast.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36810&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `A vessel entering any port ^1[not being a major port] subject to`
  line `this Act ^2*** in ballast and not carrying passengers shall be charged with a port-due at a rate to be`
  line `determined by the ^3[Government] and not exceeding three-fourths of the rate with which she would`
  line `otherwise be chargeable.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 1997, s. 7 (w.e.f. 9-1-1997).`
  line
  line `2. Certain words omitted by the A.O. 1937.`
  line
  line `3. Subs., ibid., for "Local Government".`
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (36811)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Port-due on vessels not discharging or taking in cargo.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36811&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `When a vessel enters a port`
  line `^2[not being a major port] subject to this Act, but does not discharge or take in any cargo or`
  line `passengers therein (with the exception of such unshipment and reshipment as may be necessary`
  line `for purposes of repair), she shall be charged with a port-due at a rate to be determined by the`
  line `^1[Government] and not exceeding half the rate with which she would otherwise be chargeable.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs., ibid., for "Local Government".`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 15 of 1997, s. 8 (w.e.f. 9-1-1997).`
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (36812)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Port-due not to be chargeable in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36812&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `No port-due shall be chargeable in`
  line `respect of--`
  line
  line `(a) any pleasure yacht, or`
  line
  line `(b) any vessel which, having left any port, is compelled to re -enter it by stress of`
  line `whether or in consequence of having sustained any damage, or`
  line
  line `(c) any vessel which, having entered ^1[any port ^2[in the territories which, immediately before the`
  line `1st November, 1956, were comprised in the States of Madras and Andhra] or the Port of Gopalpur in`
  line `the State of Orissa], leaves it within forty-eight hours without discharge or taking in any passengers`
  line `or cargo.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 35 of 1950, s. 3 and Second Schedule, for certain words.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. (No. 2), 1956, for "in the State of Madras or in the State of Andhra". The words in italics were ins. by the`
  line `Andhra (Adaptation of Laws on Union Subjects) Order, 1954 (w.e.f. 1-10-1953)`
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (36813)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Power to impose hospital port-dues.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36813&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1[Central Government] may, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, order that there shall be paid in respect of every vessel entering any port subject to`
  line `this Act, within a reasonable distance of which there is a public hospital or dispensary suitable for the reception or relief of seamen requiring medical aid, such further port-dues not exceeding one anna per ton`
  line `as the ^2[Central Government] thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) Such port-dues shall be called hospital port-dues, and the ^2[Central Government] shall, in`
  line `making any order under sub-section (1), have regard to any contributions made under section 36,`
  line `sub-section (5), clause (d).`
  line
  line `(3) An order imposing or increasing hospital port-dues shall not take effect till the expiration of sixty`
  line `days from the day on which the order was published in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(4) Whenever the ^2[Central Government] is satisfied that proper provision has been made`
  line `by the owners or agents of any class of vessels for giving medical aid to the seamen employed`
  line `on board such class of vessels, or that such provision is unnecessary in the case of any class of`
  line `vessels, it may, by notification in the Official Gazette, exempt such class of vessels from any`
  line `payment under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs., ibid., for "Local Government".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Government".`
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (36814)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Application and account of hospital port-dues.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Government"`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36814&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) Hospital port-dues shall be applied,`
  line `as the ^1[Central Government] may direct, to the support of any such hospital or dispensary as`
  line `aforesaid, or otherwise for providing sanitary superintendence and medical aid for the shipping in`
  line `the port in which they are levied and for the seamen belonging to the vessels therein, whether`
  line `such seamen arc ashore or afloat.`
  line
  line `(2) The ^1[Central Government] shall publish annually in the Official Gazette, as soon after the first`
  line `day of April as may be, an account, for the past financial year, of the sums received as hospital port-dues`
  line `at each port where such dues arc payable, and of the expenditure charged against those receipts.`
  line
  line `(3) Such account shall be published as a supplement to the abstract published under section 36,`
  line `sub-section (2).`
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (36815)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Master to hoist number of vessel.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36815&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) The master of every inward or outward bound`
  line `vessel, on arriving within signal distance of any signal-station established within the limits of the`
  line `river Hooghly, or within the limits of any part of a river or channel leading to a port subject to this`
  line `Act, shall, on the requisition of the pilot in charge of the vessel, signify the name of the vessel by`
  line `hoisting the number by which she is known, or by adopting such other means to t his end as may be`
  line `practicable and usual, and shall keep the signal flying until it is answered from the signal-station.`
  line
  line `(2) If the master of a vessel arriving as aforesaid offends against sub-section (1), he shall be`
  line `punishable for every such offence with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (36816)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Pilot to require master to hoist number.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36816&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every pilot in charge of a vessel shall require the`
  line `number of the vessel to be duly signalled as provided by the last foregoing section.`
  line
  line `(2) When, on such requisition from the pilot, the master refuses to hoist the number of a`
  line `vessel, or to adopt such other means of making her name known as may be practicable and`
  line `usual, the pilot may, on arrival at the first place of safe anchorage, anchor the vessel and refuse`
  line `to proceed on his course until the requisition has been complied with.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (36817)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Penalty on pilot disobeying provisions of this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36817&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `Any pilot incharge of a vessel`
  line `who disobeys, or abets disobedience to, any of the provisions of this Chapter, shall be punishable`
  line `with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees for each instance of such disobedience or`
  line `abetment, and, in addition, shall be liable to have his authority to act as a pilot withdrawn.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (36818)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Penalty for disobedience to rules and orders of the Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36818&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `If any person`
  line `disobeys any rule or order which a ^1[Government] has made in pursuance of this Act and for the punishment of disobedience to which express provision has not been made elsewhere in this Act,`
  line `he shall be punishable for every such offence with fine which may extend to one hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (36819)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Offences how triable, and penalties how recovered.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36819&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `All offences against this Act shall`
  line `be triable by a Magistrate, and any Magistrate may, by warrant under his hand, cause the amount`
  line `of any fine imposed upon the owner or master of any vessel, for any offence committed on board`
  line `of the vessel or in the management thereof or otherwise in relation thereto, whereof the owner or`
  line `master is convicted, to be levied by distress and sale of the vessel, and the tackle, apparel and`
  line `furniture thereof, or so much thereof as is necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (36820)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Costs of conviction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36820&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) In case of any conviction under this Act, the convicting`
  line `Magistrate may order the offender to pay the costs of the conviction in addition to any fine or`
  line `expenses to which he may be liable.`
  line
  line `(2) Such costs may be assessed by the Magistrate and may be recovered in the same`
  line `manner as any fine under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (36821)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Ascertainment and recovery of expenses and damages payable under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36821&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any`
  line `dispute arises as to the sum to be paid in any case as expenses or damages under this Act, it shall be`
  line `determined by a Magistrate upon application made to him for that purpose by either of the disputing`
  line parties.
  line
  line `(2) Whenever any person is liable to pay any sum, not exceeding one thousand rupees, as expenses or`
  line `damages under this Act, any Magistrate, upon application made to him by the authority to whom the sum`
  line `is payable, may, in addition to or instead of any other means for enforcing payment, recover the sum as if`
  line `it were a fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (36822)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Costs of distress.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36822&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any fine, expenses or damages is or are levied under this Act, by`
  line `distress and sale, the cost of the distress and sale may be levied in addition to such fine, expenses or`
  line `damages, and in the same manner.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (36823)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Magistrate to determine the amount to be levied in case of dispute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36823&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `If any dispute`
  line `arises concerning the amount leviable by any distress or arrest under this Act or .the costs payable`
  line `under the last foregoing section, the person making the distress or using the arrest may detain the`
  line `goods distrained or arrested, or the proceeds of the sale thereof, until the amount to be levied has`
  line `been determined by a Magistrate, who, upon application made to him for that purpose, may`
  line `determine the amount, and award such costs to be paid by either of the parties to the other of them`
  line `as he thinks reasonable, and payment of such costs, if not paid on demand, shall be enforced as if`
  line `they were a fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (36824)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Jurisdiction over offences beyond local limits of jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36824&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person offending`
  line `against the provisions of this Act in any port subject to this Act shall be punishable by any Magistrate`
  line `having jurisdiction over any district .or place adjoining the port.`
  line
  line `(2) Such Magistrate may exercise all the powers of a Magistrate under this Act, in the same manner`
  line `and to the same extent as if the offence had been committed locally within the limits of his jurisdiction,`
  line `notwithstanding that the offence may not have been committed locally within such limits, and, in case`
  line `any such Magistrate exercises the jurisdiction hereby vested in him, the offence shall be deemed, for all`
  line `purposes, to have been committed locally within the limits of his jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (36825)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Conviction to be quashed oil merits only.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36825&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `(1) No conviction, order or judgment of any`
  line `Magistrate under this Act shall be quashed for error of form or procedure, but only on the merits, and it`
  line `shall not be necessary to state, on the face of the conviction, order or judgment, the evidence on which it`
  line proceeds.
  line
  line `(2) If no jurisdiction appears on the face of the conviction, order or judgment, but the depositions`
  line `taken supply that defect, the conviction, order or judgment shall be aided by what so appears in the`
  line depositions.
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (36826)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Hoisting unlawful colours in port.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36826&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any vessel belonging to ^1[any citizen of India or`
  line `commonwealth citizen] or sailing under ^2[Indian or British colours], hoists, carries or wears, within`
  line `the limits of any port subject to this Act, any flag, jack, pennant or colours, the use whereof on board`
  line `such vessel has been prohibited by the Merchant Shipping Act, 1894 (57 & 58 Viet., c. 60) or any`
  line `other Statute now or hereafter to be in force, or by any proclamation made or to be made in`
  line `pursuance of any such Statute, or by any of ^3[the regulations] in force for the time being, the master`
  line `of the vessel shall, for every such offence, be punishable with fine .which may extend to fifty rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Such fine shall be in addition to any other penalty recoverable in respect of such an offence.`
  line
  line `(3) The conservator of the port, or any officer of ^4[the Indian Navy], may enter on board any such`
  line `vessel and seize and take away any flag, jack, pennant or colours so unlawfully hoisted, carried or worn`
  line `on board the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "any of His Majesty's subjects".`
  line
  line `2. Subs., ibid., for "British colors".`
  line
  line `3. Subs., ibid., for "His Majesty's regulations".`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "His Majesty's Navy or the Royal Indian Navy".`
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (36827)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Foreign deserters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes `1. Ins., ibid.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36827&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `Any Magistrate, upon an application being made to him by the Consul`
  line `of any foreign Power to which section 238 of the Merchant Shipping Act, 1894 (57 & 58 Vict., c.`
  line `60) has, by an Order in Council ^1[or order], been, or shall hereafter be, declared to be applicable, or`
  line `by the representative of such Consul, and upon complaint on oath of the desertion of any seaman.`
  line `not being a slave, from any vessel of such Foreign Power, may, until a revocation of such order in`
  line `Council ^1[or order] has been publicly notified, issue his warrant for the apprehension of any such`
  line `deserter, and, upon due proof of the desertion, may order him to be conveyed on board the vessel`
  line `to which he belongs or, at the instance of the Consul, to be detained in custody until the vessel is`
  line `ready to sail, or, if the vessel has sailed, for a reasonable time not exceeding one month:`
  line
  line `Provided that a deposit be first made of such sum as the Magistrate deems necessary for the`
  line `subsistence of the deserter during the detention and that the detention of the deserter shall not be`
  line `continued beyond twelve weeks.`
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (36828)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Application of sections 10 and 21.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36828&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of sections 10 and 21 shall be applicable`
  line `to all ports heretofore or hereafter declared by the ^1[Government] to be ports for the shipment and landing`
  line `of goods but not otherwise subject to this Act, and may be enforced by any Magistrate to whose ordinary`
  line `jurisdiction any such port is subject.`
  line
  line `(2) Any penalties imposed by him, and any expenses incurred by his order, under the said provisions,`
  line `shall be recoverable respectively in the manner provided in sections 55 and 57.`
  line
  line `(3) In any of the said ports for the shipment and landing of goods the consent referred to in`
  line `section 21, sub-section (4), may be given by the principal officer of customs at such port or by any other`
  line `officer appointed in that behalf by the ^1[Government].`
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (36829)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Grant of sites for sailors‟ institutes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes `1. Subs., ibid., for "with the previous sanction of the Local Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36829&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `Any local authority in which any immovable`
  line `property in or near a port is vested may, ^1[with the previous sanction, in the case of cantonment`
  line `authority or the port authority of a major port, of the Central Government, and in other cases, of the`
  line `State Government], appropriate and either retain and apply, or transfer by way of gift or otherwise,`
  line `the whole or any part of the property as a site for, or for use as, a sailors home or other institution`
  line `for the health, recreation and temporal well-being of sailors.`
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (36830)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Exercise of powers of conservator by his assistants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36830&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `(1) All acts, orders or directions by`
  line `this Act authorized to be done or given by any conservator may, subject to his control, be done or`
  line `given by any harbour-master, or any deputy- or assistant of such conservator or harbour-master.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person authorised by this Act to do any act may call to his aid such assistance as may be`
  line necessary.
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (36831)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Service of written notices of directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36831&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `Any written notice of direction given under this Act,`
  line `left for the master of any vessel with any person employed on board thereof, or affixed on a conspicuous`
  line `place on board of the vessel, shall, for the purposes of this Act, be deemed to have been given to the`
  line `master thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (36832)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Publication of orders of Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Local Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36832&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `Every declaration, order and rule of a ^1[Government]`
  line `made in pursuance of this Act shall be published in the Official Gazette, and a copy thereof shall be kept`
  line `in the office of the conservator and at the custom-house, if any, of every port to which the declaration,`
  line `order or rule relates, and shall there be open at all reasonable times to the inspection of any person`
  line `without payment of any fee.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_a:
  sectionId (36839)
  sectionNo 68A
  orderNo 69
  title `Authorities exercising jurisdiction in ports to co-operate in manoeuvres for defence of port.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 6 of 1916, s. 11.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36839&sectionno=68A&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_68_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[68A. Authorities exercising jurisdiction in ports to co-operate in manoeuvers for`
  line `defence of port.--Every authority exercising any powers or jurisdiction in. or relating to, any`
  line `port to which this Act for the time being applies shall, if so required by an officer authorised by`
  line `general or special order of the Central Government in this behalf, co -operate in such manner, as`
  line `such officer may direct, in carrying out any manoeuvers in connection with any scheme or`
  line `preparations for the defence of the said port in time of war, and for this purpose shall, if so`
  line `required, temporarily place at the disposal of such officer the services of any of its staff and the`
  line `use of any of its vessels, property, equipment or other material:`
  line
  line `Provided, firstly, that if any vessels arc placed at the disposal of such officer in accordance`
  line `with this section, the Central Government shall, in respect of the period during which they are so`
  line `at his disposal, bear the running expenses of such vessels, and be responsible for any damage`
  line thereto.
  line
  line `Explanation.--The expression 'running expenses' in this proviso includes all outlay incurred`
  line `in connection with the use of the vessels other than any charges for their hire, or for the wages`
  line `of the officers and crews of such vessels:`
  line
  line `Provided, secondly, that any officer making a requisition under this section shall exercise`
  line `his powers in such a way as to cause as little disturbance to the ordinary business of the port as`
  line `is compatible with the exigencies of the efficient carrying out of the manoeuvers:`
  line
  line `Provided, thirdly, that no suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against any authority for`
  line `any default occurring by reason only of compliance with a requisition under this section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_68_b:
  sectionId (36834)
  sectionNo 68B
  orderNo 70
  title `Duties of the said authorities in an emergency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 6 of 1916, s. 11.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36834&sectionno=68B&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_68_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[68B. Duties of the said authorities in an emergency.--Whenever the Central Government`
  line `is of opinion that an emergency has arisen which renders it necessary that the duties imposed for`
  line `the purposes specified in section 68A on the authorities therein mentioned, or other duties of a`
  line `like nature, should be imposed on such authorities continuously during the existence of the`
  line `emergency, it may, by general or special order, authorise any officer to require the. said`
  line `authorities to perform such duties until the Central Government is of opinion that the`
  line `emergency has passed, and the said authority shall comply accordingly, and the provisions of`
  line `the said section shall apply subject to the following modification, namely: --`
  line
  line `The Central Government shall pay any authority, on whom a requisition has been made,`
  line `such compensation for any loss or damage attributable to such requisition, and for any`
  line `services rendered or expenditure incurred in complying therewith as, in default of agreement,`
  line `shall be decided to be just and reasonable, having regar d to the circumstances of the case, by`
  line `the arbitration of a person to be nominated in this behalf by the Central Government, and the`
  line `decision of such person shall be final.]`
obj_root_law_sections_68_c:
  sectionId (36835)
  sectionNo 68C
  orderNo 71
  title `Application of certain provisions of the Act to aircraft.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 35 of 1951, s. 192.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36835&sectionno=68C&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_68_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[68C. Application of certain provisions of the Act to aircraft.--(1) The provisions of`
  line `sections 6, 13 to 16 (both inclusive), 18, 21 and 28, sub-section (2) of section 31 and sections 33,`
  line `34, 35, 39, 42 to 48 (both inclusive) and 55 shall apply in relation to all aircraft making use of any`
  line `port subject to this Act, while on water as they apply in relation to vessels.`
  line
  line `(2) No such aircraft shall enter or leave any port subject to this Act, except with the`
  line `permission granted by the Conservator of the Port or by such other officer as may be`
  line `authorized in this behalf by the Conservator.]`
obj_root_law_sections_68_d:
  sectionId (36836)
  sectionNo 68D
  orderNo 72
  title `Maritime seruity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 2007, s. 7.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881&sectionId=36836&sectionno=68D&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_0_00019_190815_1523340712881
obj_root_law_sections_68_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[68D. Maritime security.--A port facility in India shall comply with all the requirements`
  line `contained in Chapter IXB of the Merchant Shipping Act, 1958 (44 of 1958) or the rules made`
  line `thereunder so far as they are not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section, the expression "port facility" shall have the`
  line `same meaning as assigned to it in Part IXB of the Merchant Shipping Act, 1958 (44 of 1958).`
